rlink ARPU (Average Revenue Per User):** \n    *   Q1 2026: $66 per month (down from $86 in Q1 2025)\n    *   FY 2025: $81 per month (down from $91 in FY 2024 and $99 in FY 2023)\n*   **Satellite Count:** Approximately 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit (LEO) as of March 31, 2026 (~9,000 are broadband-specific). Launched approximately 3,100 satellites in 2025.\n*   **Geographic Reach:** 164 countries, territories, and other markets.\n*   **Satellite-to-Mobile Supported Accounts/Devices:** Approximately 7.4 million monthly unique devices across approximately 30 countries.\n*   **Network Throughput & Performance:** Median latency of ~25 milliseconds; median download speed of 225 Mbps during peak hours for residential users; download speeds exceeding 400 Mbps with round-trip latencies as low as 21 milliseconds.\n\n**Financial KPIs:**\n*   **Segment Income from Operations:** $1,188 million in Q1 2026; $4,423 million in FY 2025.\n*   **Segment Adjusted EBITDA:** $2,087 million in Q1 2026; $7,168 million in FY 2025.\n*   **Revenue (Q1 2026):** $3,257 million total (Consumer: $2,148M, Enterprise & Government: $1,109M).\n\n### 3. AI Segment (xAI)\n**Key Operating Metrics:**\n*   **Nameplate Compute Draw:** \n    *   Q1 2026: 1 gigawatt (up from 0.3 in Q1 2025)\n    *   FY 2025: 0.8 gigawatts (up from 0.3 in FY 2024 and 0 in FY 2023)\n    *   *Note:* This metric reflects installed capacity (GPUs multiplied by all-in power draw) and does not represent actual power consumption. The 1.0 GW capacity was reached by bringing COLOSSUS and COLOSSUS II online.\n*   *Note on missing metrics:* While the text mentions the frontier LLM Grok and real-time information platform X, it does not provide specific quantitative metrics for AI tokens, AI user counts, or AI-specific throughput in this chunk.\n\n**Financial KPIs:**\n*   **Segment Loss from Operations:** $(2,469) million in Q1 2026; $(6,355) million in FY 2025.\n*   **Segment Adjusted EBITDA:** $(609) million in Q1 2026; $(1,237) million in FY 2025.\n*   **Revenue (Q1 2026):** $818 million total (Advertising: $343M, AI Solutions & Infrastructure: $475M).',
