r as services are consumed for usage-based arrangements.\n*   **Advertising:** Recognized in the period the advertising is delivered, as evidenced by a user engaging with the ad. Contract terms are typically cancellable short-term arrangements.\n\n**4. Pricing Models**\n*   **Grok Business and Grok Enterprise:** Sold on **license-**, **consumption-**, or **outcome-based** pricing models.\n*   **Grok Consumer Subscriptions:** Priced on a monthly or annual basis across four tiers: basic, SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy, and SuperGrok Lite. Higher pricing tiers unlock expanded access to advanced models, increased usage limits, priority compute, and premium features.\n\n**5. Operational Metrics and Infrastructure**\n*   **Grok Business, Grok Enterprise, and xAI Gov:** These offerings are designed to scale with enterprise and governmental AI adoption. The company intends to support them with a specialized salesforce and forward-deployed engineers who embed directly with clients to implement solutions.\n*   **API Access (Grok API):** Enables developers to integrate Grok models directly into external software applications and workflows.\n*   **AI Computational Infrastructure:**\n    *   The company operates a highly vertically integrated AI platform spanning gigawatt-scale AI compute infrastructure.\n    *   Its facilities, **COLOSSUS** and **COLOSSUS II** (located in Memphis, Tennessee), collectively provide approximately **1.0 gigawatt** of compute power, with additional power capacity available for data center operations.\n    *   The first cluster of COLOSSUS was brought online in 122 days.\n    *   COLOSSUS II will provide the compute needed to train the next-generation Grok 5 AI model.\n*   **User and Product Engagement Metrics:**\n    *   Integrated AI platforms across Grok and X have over **1.3 billion supported accounts** active in the last twelve months ended March 31, 2026.\n    *   Approximately **550 million Monthly Active Users (MAUs)** as of March 31, 2026 (up from 520 million MAUs as of December 31, 2025).\n    *   Approximately **117 million MAUs** used Grok’s AI features as of March 31, 2026.\n    *   Grok's image and video generation system, Imagine, produced approximately **10 billion images and over 2 billion videos per month**, on average, for the quarter ending March 31, 2026.",
